Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian I (Half-time - Contract) Vancouver , BC Description Since 1936 Columbia College has offered quality educational programs designed to prepare students for university admission. These programs include a University Transfer Program fully integrated into the BC Transfer System and a Secondary Program Certified by the Province of British Columbia. Thousands of Canadian and international students have progressed through Columbia’s programs to successful Canadian universities. Librarian I (Half-Time – Contract) OPPORTUNITY: Columbia College Library is seeking a Half-time Librarian to serve as part of our team and assist in all areas of Library operation. Due to our extensive and important Information Literacy program, we are looking for a candidate who can quickly come up to speed on our classroom and Moodle lessons, adding to and improving our offerings. In partnership with the other members of our team, this position with at times, cover circulation, provide reference services, assist with outreach and events, participate in collection development, and troubleshoot technology. This opportunity would suit a new Librarian interested in exploring a wide variety of job duties and areas of responsibility. The term of appointment for this position will start in March 2024 and end in August 2024. This position might be extended for an additional semester. KEY RESPONSIBILITIES: Planning, delivering and assessing Library-led Information Literacy lessons in accordance with current best practices and guiding principlesPlanning, creating and updating digital learning objects, including video tutorials, web pages, learning modules, and instructional materials for the use of students and facultyProviding research support services in-person and via email, phone, video, or chatParticipating in the selection, acquisition and management of print and electronic information resourcesParticipating in planning and delivering programs and events in the Library and CollegeServing as a backup for Electronic Services LibrarianSupporting the Indigenization activities of the Library and College IDEAL CANDIDATE: The ideal candidate for this position has: An ALA-accredited MLIS degree or equivalent Experience providing library instruction incorporating UDL and a trauma-informed perspective Knowledge of ACRL’s Framework for Information Literacy for Higher Education and methods for instruction assessment Experience providing research support to international students A track record of successful Indigenization and EDI work in a post-secondary context The ability to creatively problem-solve and implement effective solutions The ability to handle multiple projects and competing priorities Excellent interpersonal and written/verbal communication skills Dedication to providing high-quality, friendly customer service The ability to exercise good judgment Flexibility and a team-orientation HOURS OF WORK: This is a 17.5 hours/week position. The working schedule will be: Monday from 11:00 am to 7:00 pmFriday from 9:00 am to 5:00 pmSaturday from 1:30 pm to 5:00 pm Some flexibility with the hours may be required. COMPENSATION: In addition to working with an inclusive, progressive group of people, we offer a competitive salary based on qualifications and experience. This position’s annual part-time gross salary range is $33,036.90 - $43,029.29. APPLICATION PROCEDURE: Please submit your application, including a cover letter and resume, through our portal https://www.columbiacollege.ca/careers/ Please note that filling out the entire profile is not mandatory in order to upload the required resume and cover letter on the platform. For additional information about the application process, please check Columbia College Application Process Application Deadline: March 7, 2024 At Columbia College, we foster a culture of equity, diversity and inclusion. The College invites and encourages applications from all qualified individuals, including groups traditionally underrepresented in employment, who may contribute to the further diversification of our Institution. We thank all applicants for their interest in the position; only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $33,036.90 - $43,029.29 Closes: 7 March, 2024 Columbia College Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
