Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Part Time Branch Assistant Clinton , ON Description The County of Huron’sCultural Services-Library Departmentis seeking aPart-Time Library Branch Assistant to Join the West Team!The library’s Team is currently hiring for a part-time branch assistant for the Goderich, and Bayfield branches for approximately 16-21 hours per week. Shifts will include some weekdays, weekends, and evenings. Schedule is subject to change to meet the needs of the library.Typical Schedule:Monday: Goderich Branch 3:15-8:15 (5)Tuesday: Bayfield Branch 12:00-4:00 &amp; Goderich Branch 5:15-8:15 (7)Friday: Bayfield Branch 9:45-2:15 (4.5)Alternating Saturday’s: Bayfield Branch 9:45-2:15 (4.5)What We Offer:At the County of Huron, we’re committed to offering a modern work environment that puts people first. We are a Certified Living Wage employer that values equity, diversity and inclusion. We offer our staff competitive wages and a comprehensive benefits package.The County of Huron offers a diverse portfolio of employment opportunities. When you join our team, you’ll have the benefit of working with and learning from, people who have a broad range of skills and knowledge. We offer training, mentorship, and career development opportunities to all staff. When you work for the County of Huron, you invest in the community, and you benefit from seeing the results of your efforts firsthand. It’s a great place to work!Learn more about working for the County of Huron: https://vimeo.com/699170923Position Summary:Provides public library service to the community and surrounding area at branch libraries by providing front desk circulation service, reference, information, readers’ advisory and technology support services. Develops community connections to inform creation of programs and services. Assists with collection maintenance.Duties will include:Reference and Readers’ advisory services, including assisting patrons to find information in all formats.Provides technical assistance to library users on all platforms.Uses creativity to develop, prepare and deliver library programs.Markets the library collection through displays and at-desk promotion.Introduces new members to the library and explains services.Maintains up-to-date and confidential membership records.Notifies patrons of overdue materials and arrival of requested materials.Negotiates any problems as required in the absence of the branch manager.Ensures collection is in good condition and relevant through ongoing collection maintenance.Works in more than one branch library and may be responsible for a branch library in the absence of the branch manager.Performs other duties as required by the branch manager.Qualifications:Post secondary training in public library services, including library technician (Community College, 2 years), or excel program in small library management.2 years experience (3000 hours) working with the public; familiarity with library service an asset.Clear Vulnerable Sector Check and become Safe Places Youth CertifiedPreferred Skills:Ability to troubleshoot new technologies.Excellent customer service skillsExcellent communication and people skillsAbility to collaborate as part of a teamCreativity and ability to be flexible on the jobProficiency in computer use, including Microsoft Office Products, Outlooks, Zoom, OneDrive, electronic databases, internet browsers and library automation systems.Ability to sell ideas/library servicesCompetitive Compensation:$28.98 – $33.91 per hour, as per the 2023 non-union pay gridOpportunity to opt into an OMERS pensionPlease forward a cover letter and resume by 4:30 pm on Friday March 1, 2024 to humanresources [at] huroncounty [ dot ] caSubmissions guidelines:To be considered for this position, please ensure:the email subject line is “2024 Branch Assistant”the cover letter is a maximum of one page longthe cover letter and resume are saved together in one pdf filethe pdf file name is your: First name and Last name (e.g. “Jane Smith.pdf”)We look forward to hearing from you!Posted February 15, 2024.Don’t meet every single requirement?Studies have shown that women are less likely to apply for jobs unless they meet every single qualification. If you’re excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may just be the right candidate for this or other roles. At the County of Huron, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace.Only those individuals selected for an interview will be contacted. Information is collected solely for the purpose of job selection under the provisions of the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act. The County of Huron is an equal opportunity employer. Accessibility accommodations are available for all parts of the recruitment process. Applicants need to make their needs known in advance. Compensation $29.98-$33.91 per hour Closes: 1 March, 2024 Huron County Library Clinton , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
