Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Director of Legal Resources Winnipeg , MB Description MANITOBA LAW LIBRARY INC. The Manitoba Law Library, located in the Winnipeg Law Courts complex, is the law library for the legal profession in Manitoba. We are funded by the Law Society of Manitoba and support their mandate to protect the public by ensuring lawyers have access to essential legal research tools. The library is used primarily by lawyers but is also open to self-representing litigants and those conducting legal research. DIRECTOR OF LEGAL RESOURCES The Director of Legal Resources leads, directs and administers the programs and services of the Manitoba Law Library Inc. They are responsible to plan, develop and manage a comprehensive library system including facilities, operations, and programs that address the needs of members of the Law Society of Manitoba and the public seeking legal information; to secure and manage fiscal resources and oversee administration of the library’s budget; to ensure alignment with the Society’s vision, mission, goals and values; to take a visible role in representing the library in the legal community; and determining service and program priorities. This position reports directly to the Chief Executive Officer of the Manitoba Law Library Inc., who is also the Chief Executive Officer of the Law Society of Manitoba. The ideal candidate will possess the following: Knowledge of the principles and practices of leadership, management, and administration with specific knowledge in the delivery of law library services;Knowledge and experience in delivering legal research services; Skill in promoting innovative, forward-thinking ideas;Skill in fostering a welcoming culture that engages the broad diversity of the community;Skill in fostering a participatory work environment in which individuals collaborate in pursuit of a common mission and shared goals;Skill in written and verbal communication and the ability to make presentations before members of the legal profession, the public, and staff;Ability and skill in visioning, strategic planning, proactive community engagement and project implementation;Demonstrated ability to lead, plan, organize, coordinate and manage the staff and programs of a small organization;Ability to articulate the Society’s vision in the area of Access to Justice, and develop and maintain effective working relationships with similar organizations;Demonstrated ability to analyze, prepare and manage a comprehensive budget;Ability to develop and identify creative solutions and opportunities to increase available resources;Ability to analyze complex problems and situations and develop and implement effective solutions. Qualifications Education: Masters Degree in Library or Information Sciences, or a Library Technician Diploma plus five years experience in a library with increasing levels of responsibility Experience: Minimum five years’ progressively responsible experience in library services, preferably in a law library. Must pass a Criminal Record check. Salary range: $65,000-85,000/year The Manitoba Law Library believes in supporting our team by offering a comprehensive compensation package including a competitive salary, pension, group benefits package, career development and training opportunities and a positive work-life balance philosophy. We recognize that diverse opinions, abilities, identities, cultures and languages in our profession and workplace are a critical foundation to an effective and equitable society and encourage all qualified candidates to apply. The Manitoba Law Library Inc. welcomes applications from people with disabilities.Disability accommodations are available upon request. To Apply: Please submit a resume and cover letter by 5:00 p.m. CST, February 26, 2024 to: Karen Sawatzky Director of Legal Resources ksawatzky@lawsociety.mb.ca To learn more visit https://lawlibrary.ca/. The Manitoba Law Library Inc. thanks all applicants for their interest. Please note that only those applicants selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $65,000 - $85,000 Closes: 26 February, 2024 Manitoba Law Library Inc. Winnipeg , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
